00:03:41.190 --> 00:03:44.300
A question that was actually
central to the development

00:03:44.300 --> 00:03:47.110
of sociology and social theory.

00:03:47.110 --> 00:03:49.920
So what happens to religion
in the modern world?

00:03:49.920 --> 00:03:52.760
How do religions response
to modernity?

00:03:52.760 --> 00:03:56.440
And for centuries the answer
read along a very binary track,

00:03:56.440 --> 00:04:00.270
so in their responses to
modernity religions were expected

00:04:00.270 --> 00:04:03.680
to either reject it, and that's
what we call fundamentalism,

00:04:03.680 --> 00:04:06.990
to preserve the tradition or they
would secularize the tradition

00:04:06.990 --> 00:04:10.680 position:56%
and accommodate modernity and that's
what we call liberal religion.

00:04:10.680 --> 00:04:13.250
And even though this binary
track was mostly based

00:04:13.250 --> 00:04:16.840
on the Christian experience,
it's also applied to Islam,

00:04:16.840 --> 00:04:20.510
but when it's applied to Islam it's
a little bit modified given the

00:04:20.510 --> 00:04:23.960
perception of Islam as a
special religion, which is --

00:04:23.960 --> 00:04:26.340
that Islam is intrinsically
anti-modern

00:04:26.340 --> 00:04:30.100
and intrinsically secularization
resistant.

00:04:30.100 --> 00:04:33.600
So given this the divide
and modifies into the idea

00:04:33.600 --> 00:04:36.540
that Islam gears towards
rejection of modernity

00:04:36.540 --> 00:04:39.000
and Islamic fundamentalism
or Islamic rejection

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:42.530
of modernity itself is geared
towards politically takeover

00:04:42.530 --> 00:04:44.000
of the state.

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:46.260
So accordingly then if Islam is

00:04:46.260 --> 00:04:49.530
to engage modernity it
must loosen orthodoxy more

00:04:49.530 --> 00:04:53.440
than any other religion while
also making a cultural turn.

00:04:53.440 --> 00:04:57.940
So that also created yet another
divide, cultural versus political.

00:04:57.940 --> 00:04:59.680
And this kind of framework,

00:04:59.680 --> 00:05:05.680
this kind of abstract framework
crystallized into the concept

00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:09.050
of moderate Islam more
recently and turkey is picked

00:05:09.050 --> 00:05:11.440
as the most prominent
candidates for it.

00:05:11.440 --> 00:05:15.000
And the concept has been helpful
to some extent in communicating

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:17.150
that Islam needs not
to reject modernity,

00:05:17.150 --> 00:05:19.010
but actually can engage it.

00:05:19.010 --> 00:05:21.850
But there are various problems
with the concept moderate Islam.

00:05:21.850 --> 00:05:24.630
First of all, it reinforces
the divide of fundamentalist

00:05:24.630 --> 00:05:29.210
versus a liberal religion, because
radical moderation of Islam happens

00:05:29.210 --> 00:05:32.760
through the pacification
of its radical aspects.

00:05:32.760 --> 00:05:37.040
So meaning that the practice of
moderate is something less Islamic

00:05:37.040 --> 00:05:39.290
and more liberal than the norm.

00:05:39.290 --> 00:05:42.410
So apparently this marginalizes
any deeply held religion

00:05:42.410 --> 00:05:47.110
and it simply has religion
actually must be fundamentalist.

00:05:47.110 --> 00:05:50.370
Also another problem with the
term is that the conditions

00:05:50.370 --> 00:05:52.630
for moderate Islam
is constantly being

00:05:52.630 --> 00:05:54.480
or at least mostly is being looked

00:05:54.480 --> 00:05:57.900
out from outside, rather
than from within.

00:05:57.900 --> 00:06:01.870
And most interpretations
rely on political expediency

00:06:01.870 --> 00:06:06.140
and political actors in trying to
understand how moderation happens.

00:06:06.140 --> 00:06:07.920
But there's a serious
problem with that

00:06:07.920 --> 00:06:11.110
because party failure is
then seen as Islam's failure

00:06:11.110 --> 00:06:15.170 position:56%
in engaging modernity and the Arab
spring was probably the epic example

00:06:15.170 --> 00:06:16.470
of that.

00:06:16.470 --> 00:06:18.290
The cultural sentiments
that could not translate

00:06:18.290 --> 00:06:21.880
into political change were
that interpreted again,

00:06:21.880 --> 00:06:23.640
yet again as Islam's failure

00:06:23.640 --> 00:06:26.830
into engaging modern
life and institutions.

00:06:26.830 --> 00:06:31.200
But most importantly the concept
of moderate Islam prevents us

00:06:31.200 --> 00:06:35.290
from seeing the empirical
complexities of religion in Turkey,

00:06:35.290 --> 00:06:41.030
but also about more broadly
Islam's engagements of modernity.

00:06:41.030 --> 00:06:45.320
So in my book, "Looking at Post
80's Islamic Transformation

00:06:45.320 --> 00:06:50.610
of Islamic Identity in
Turkey," I argued that's rather

00:06:50.610 --> 00:06:53.190
than normatively or
generically defining what's going

00:06:53.190 --> 00:06:56.390
on as moderate Islam, what
we're witnessing is the rise

00:06:56.390 --> 00:07:00.300
of any religious form, indeed
in your religious orthodoxy.

00:07:00.300 --> 00:07:03.060
And when I say "in orthodoxy,"
I don't mean the separation

00:07:03.060 --> 00:07:05.580
between orthodoxy of an
orthopractic religions.

00:07:05.580 --> 00:07:09.690
I simply denote a commitment
to the super empirical,

00:07:09.690 --> 00:07:11.520
but this orthodoxy is new

00:07:11.520 --> 00:07:14.240
because it's neither fundamentalist
rejection of modernity,

00:07:14.240 --> 00:07:16.840
nor liberal submission to it.

00:07:16.840 --> 00:07:21.010
Indeed within the Turkish context
I call this new form Muslimism

00:07:21.010 --> 00:07:26.170
and I argue that this new form
embraces aspects of modern life,

00:07:26.170 --> 00:07:29.820
while submitting that life to
a sacred moral order generating

00:07:29.820 --> 00:07:33.090
as such hybrid institutions,
discourses and lifestyles

00:07:33.090 --> 00:07:37.640
and we will kind of
unpack these as we go.

00:07:37.640 --> 00:07:40.670
Now, why the term "Muslimism"?

00:07:40.670 --> 00:07:42.760
First of all, this new form looking

00:07:42.760 --> 00:07:48.840
at a liberal nor fundamentalist
required a new category.

00:07:48.840 --> 00:07:52.590
Normally, you know, Islamism
is used as a term is used

00:07:52.590 --> 00:07:55.590
as an umbrella term to define
any Islamic movement that kind

00:07:55.590 --> 00:07:58.100
